oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Shamrock Hotel
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Interior view of the guestroom at the Shamrock Hotel. Two people are standing behind the counter while a woman and man stand on the other side. A table with chairs is in the center of the room, adjacent to a sofa. The hotel was established in 1928 and operated into the 1950s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Hotels; Hotel employees
